<subSubSection pageNumber="303" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="303">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="303">Note:</emphasis>
As noted by Dahlgren (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="303">Opera Bot.</emphasis>
4: 114. 1960) and Nordenstam (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="303">Bot. Not.</emphasis>
114: 278. 1961), this is a later homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1753)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1756" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Anthyllis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lotoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="303">A. lotoides</emphasis>
L. (1753)
</taxonomicName>
, and therefore illegitimate. In 1759, Linnaeus published 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rothm." baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Aspalathus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aspalathoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="303">A. aspalathoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="303">nomen novum</emphasis>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1756)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1756" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Anthyllis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lotoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="303">A. lotoides</emphasis>
L. (1756)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
